docs.name: curasan AG (CUR)
docs.description: curasan AG is a Germany-based company that specializes in the production and distribution of drugs and medical products. The Company operates in such fields as dental implants, bone and tissue regeneration, tissue engineering, and wound healing for dental, spinal and orthopedic applications. cursan AG divides its business activities into the two segments: Pharmaceuticals and Biomaterials. Pharmaceuticals segment includes primarily the product Mitem, a drug for the treatment of urinary bladder cancer. Biomaterials segment's portfolio comprises Stypro, gelatin sponge for the control and wound healing; Curavisc, which is used for the treatment of joint arthrosis; Cerasorb, a synthetic bone substitution and regeneration material; Osbone, a spongious bone substitute, and ATR, which supports tissue regeneration. In the dental field, Cerasorb is marketed by Riemser Arzneimittel AG

docs.description:
The investment seeks total return.
 The fund selects investments from a broad spectrum of asset classes, including both traditional investments, such as equity and fixed income securities, and less traditional or alternative investments, such as commodity-oriented investments, real estate related investments, and currencies. It may invest in debt securities of any credit quality, including those rated below investment grade (known as 'junk bonds') or, if unrated, of equivalent credit quality as determined by the fund's investment adviser. The fund may invest in securities with a broad range of maturities. It is non-diversified.

docs.name: Mars Hill Global Relative Value ETF (GRV)
docs.description: Historical ETF prices for Mars Hill Global Relative Value ETF (GRV). Accuvest Global Long Short ETF (the Fund), formerly Mars Hill Global Relative Value ETF, seeks to provide average annual returns in excess of the total return of the MSCI World Index. AGLS is managed by Accuvest Global Advisors (Portfolio Manager). The Portfolio Manager seeks to achieve the Fund's objective by investing in long positions in the United States listed country-specific exchange traded funds (ETFs) combined with short positions in country-specific ETFs. The sub-advisor seeks to profit from the relative performance between long and short positions in global regions, countries, styles and sectors. Accuvest Global Advisors, LLC acts as a global manager of the Company.

docs.name: Jiangsu Hongbao Hardware Co., Ltd. (002071)
docs.description: Jiangsu Hongbao Hardware Co., Ltd. is principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of hardware products. The Company's products include hardware tools series, scissors series and kitchenware series. The hardware tools series include pliers, spanners, woodworking instruments, hammers, tool equipments and others. The scissors series include embroidery scissors, stationery scissors, hair clippers, nail-scissors, multifunctional scissors, allotypic scissors and others. The Company distributes its products in both domestic and overseas markets under brand name of Hongbao.

docs.name: Tepa Tibbi ve Elektronik Urunler (TEPAS)
docs.description: Tepa Tibbi ve Elektronik Urunler Sanayi ve Ticaret AS (Tepa) is a Turkey-based company engaged in the medical equipment sector. The Company's basic product line consists of PC-USB based ECG system and its ECG-Stress test version with treadmill. Other products, which also support the basic products, are: ECG Holder systems, ambulatory blood pressure monitoring devices (ABPM), dynamic blood pressure monitors for ECG stress testing, and bedside monitors. The Company also supplies products from local and foreign companies for hospital equipment supply projects. Kardiosis Ltd is Tepa's research and development company. The Company is a majority shareholder of Ortepa AS, an orthopedic implant supplier in Turkey.

docs.name: DI Corp (003160)
docs.description: D.I CORPORATION is a Korea-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of semiconductor inspection equipment. The Company produces semiconductor inspection equipment such as monitoring burn-in testers (MBTs), test burn-in testers (TBTs), wafer level burn-in testers (WBTs), burn-in boards (BIBs) and wafer test boards (WTBs). In addition, it produces electronic components such as electromagnetic wave shielding, electro-magnetic interference (EMI) absorbers and thermal interface materials. It also involves in the manufacture of hydro blocks, ultraviolet disinfection systems, sludge collectors and others. The Company distributes its products within domestic market and to overseas market.

docs.name: Chia Ta World Co., Ltd. (2033)
docs.description: Chia Ta World Co., Ltd is a Taiwan-based company principally engaged in the manufacturing, processing and distribution of steel products. The Company's product portfolio consists of general steel wires, galvanized steel wires, pre-stressed concrete steel wires and strands, pre-stressed concrete steel bars and galvanized and ungalvanized steel wire strands. The Company distributes its products in Taiwan market and to overseas markets, including the rest of Asia and the Americas. During the year ended December 31, 2011, the Company obtained approximately 72.2% and 23.01% of its total revenue from the sale of general steel wires and steel ropes, respectively.

docs.name: Western Ast Clymr Infl Lkd Sc & Incm Fd (WIA)
docs.description: Western Asset/Claymore Inflation-Linked Securities & Income Fund (the Fund) diversified, closed-end management investment company. The Fund's primary investment objective is to provide current income for its shareholders. It will invest at least 60% of its total managed assets in the United States Treasury Inflation Protected-Securities (TIPS). It will invest not more than 40% of its total managed assets in non-United States dollar investments, which gives the Fund the flexibility to invest up to 40% of its total managed assets in non-United States dollar inflation-linked securities. Up to 20% of the Fund's portfolio securities may represent corporate debt securities of investment grade quality at the time of their purchase that are not inflation-linked securities. Western Asset Management Company is the Fund's investment advisers.
